- "Cumulative average difficulty" is the average difficulty of all trails used by a skier, considering multiple trails;
- "Number of different trails" is the count of unique trails used by each skier.

sql:
SELECT AVG(T2.average_slope) AS average_steepness
FROM skiers AS T1
JOIN trails AS T2 ON T2.trail_name = T1.favorite_trails;

external_knowledge:
- "Popular" refers to trails used more than 10 times;
- "Highly-rated" refers to trails with an average rating greater than 4;
- "Recently approved" refers to the most recent approved version of the trail.
